==English==
===Noun===
'''irreducible complexity'''

''Irreducible Complexity'' is a more common form of the base term '''irreducibly complex''' (adjective; see [[complex]]), which was coined by [[w:Michael_J._Behe|Michael Behe]] in his 1996 book ''[[w:Darwin's_Black_Box|Darwin's Black Box: The Biochemical Challenge to Evolution]]'' as

<BLOCKQUOTE>
By ''irreducibly complex'' I mean a single system composed of several well-matched, interacting parts that contribute to the basic function, wherein the removal of any one of the parts causes the system to effectively cease functioning.
</BLOCKQUOTE>

The term is often abbreviated as [[IC]].

